  "bib_entries": {
    "87066366": {
      "title": "Prediction of B Cell Epitopes and Major Characteristics in Protein gG of M onkey Herpes B Virus",
      "abstract": "To explore the possibility of the monkey B virus gG gene encoded protein as a vaccine candidate antigen and detecting antigen for ELISA kits development,monkey herpes B virus gG gene sequences is firstly download from Genbank database. Online analysis system IEDB and SOSUI are then adopted for the gene sequence bioinformatic analysis of the coding region. The prediction is carried out on protein encoded gG gene physicochemical properties,solubility and surface accessibility,transmembrane region epitopes and linear B-cell epitopes. The results show that membrane protein gG protein herpes B virus is a soluble protein,having a transmembrane helix,and relatively rich β-corners,whose protein sequence has a plurality of antigenic epitopes and dominant B-cell linear epitopes. It has the potential to serve as a monkey B virus vaccine candidate antigen and antibody diagnostic antigen."
    }
